500|$|On board were 130 passengers, of whom 3 were children, {{consisting}} of Arktikugol employees and their families. Waiting {{at the airport}} for the return flight were 120 other employees and their families. The aircraft left Vnukovo Airport at 04:44 Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) or 08:44 Moscow Summer Time. Estimated flight time was 3 hours and 30 minutes, and alternative airports were Murmansk Airport and Severomorsk-3, both in Murmansk Oblast, Russia. The flight proceeded normally until descent, following the routing W 29 from Moscow to Padun (west of Murmansk), before crossing to Bodø <b>Flight</b> <b>Information</b> <b>Region</b> over the Barents Sea cruising at FL 350 at an average airspeed of [...] It then proceeded over Bjørnøya non-directional beacon (NDB), Isfjord NDB and Advent NDB.|$|E
